        <text>
            <body>
                <div type="edition">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/> 
                            β<supplied reason="omitted">α</supplied>σιλέως 
                            <persName>
                                <name type="praenomen" key="Alexander Ἄλεξάνδρος">
                                    <expan><abbr>Ἀλε</abbr><ex>ξάνδρου</ex></expan>
                                </name>
                            </persName>
                        <lb n="2"/>
                            ἡμεροδρόμας καὶ 
                        <lb n="3"/> 
                            βηματιστὴς τῆς <placeName>Ἀσίας</placeName>
                        <lb n="4"/>
                            <persName>
                                <name key="Philonides Φιλωνίδης">Φιλωνίδης</name>  
                                <persName>
                                    <name key="Zotes Ζωΐτης">Ζωΐτου</name>
                                </persName>
                                Κρὴς
                            <lb n="5"/>
                                <name type="ethnonym">Χερσονάσιος</name>
                            </persName>
                            ἀνέθηκε
                        <lb n="6"/>
                            Διὶ Ὀλυμπίοι.
                    </ab>
                </div>
                <div type="translation">
                    <p>Philonides, son of Zotes, from Chersonese, and a courier
                        and road-measurer for King Alexander in Asia, dedicated (this statue) to Olympian Zeus.</p>
                </div>
                <div type="commentary">
                    <p>This is the right half of the cast of the statue base, and should be read
                    with its left half NY.Ith.CU.G.CCC.485.</p>
                </div>
